section(class="template-wrapper" )
    aside(class="template-asideLeft o-aside-Item")
    |
    |
    div(class="template-section m-a" ng-init="unirColumnasFuncion()")
        section(class="template-content u-animationFadeDown")
                h5 #[strong.u-textColor_4 1. ] Watch the video:
                div(class="row-flex")
                    div(class="col-flex-sm12 col-flex-md6 col-center")

                        div(class="row-flex justify-center mt20 mb20"): div(class="col md11"): div(class="c-contVideo"): video(controls class="u-responsive-video")
                            source(src="unit_2/module_8/"+pathVideo+"act_1.mp4" type="video/mp4")

                    div(class="col-flex-sm12 col-flex-md6 col-center")
                        p Now read the following sentences. Pay attention to the use of #[strong WOULD].
                        p • When I was a child my father #[strong would ] sometimes #[strong take ] me to the Campin stadium.
                        p • We #[strong would go ] to a nearby restaurant after the games.
                        h6 #[strong.u-textColor_4 1. ] Complete and match.
                        div(class="row-flex mt50")
                            div(class="col xs12 md12 col-center" data-ejercicio="unir")
                                div(id="sourceElements" class="ancho350 js-columnas")
                                    span(id="Item0_0" class="treeItem" onclick="setSource(this)" seleccion valor="1") We use would + ___________ when we talk about activities that were frequently repeated in the past.
                                    span(id="Item0_1" class="treeItem" onclick="setSource(this)" seleccion valor="2") If the action in the past happened only once, we must use __________
                                div(id="linecanvas" style="width: 60px;")
                                div(id="targetElements" class="ancho350 js-columnas") 
                                    span(id="Item1_0" class="treeItem" onclick="setTarget(this)" seleccion valor="2") I went on a long bike ride last Saturday.
                                    span(id="Item1_1" class="treeItem" onclick="setTarget(this)" seleccion valor="1") Every Saturday, I would go on a long bike ride.
